ce:section.ce:para:
The SEM image of rGO@NCQDs derived from Moosa balbeesiaana peels revealed a mushroom-shaped structure, as shown in Fig. 4(a)
                        . The graphical illustration of the EDX analysis (Fig. 4(b)
                        ) indicates the presence of carbon (C), nitrogen (N), and oxygen (O), which significantly confirms the formation of rGO@NCQDs. The presence of silicon (Si) and potassium (K) is attributed to natural ingredients present in the Moosa balbeesiaana fruit. The weight and atomic percentage of these five elements are as follows: carbon (C)- 40.2 % (atomic percentage 51 %), nitrogen (N)−16.5 % (atomic percentage 18 %), oxygen (O)−24.7 % (atomic percentage 23.6 %), silicon (Si)−1.5 % (atomic percentage 0.8 %), and potassium (K)−17.0 % (atomic percentage 6.6 %).
